'''Harold Randall Griffith''' (July 25, 1894–1985) was a Canadian [[anesthesiologist]] and a leader in the fields of [[anesthesiology]]. 

He was born in Montreal, the son of Alexander Randall Griffith, a medical doctor and homeopathic practitioner. His own medical studies at [[McGill University]] were interrupted by World War I, when he was awarded the [[Military Medal]] for bravery at [[Vimy Ridge]].<ref name=CAS/> He graduated from [[McGill University]] in 1922, later became the first President of the Canadian Anaesthetists' Society (now Canadian Anesthesiologists' Society),<ref>http://www.cas.ca/English/CAS-Chronology</ref> and the first elected president of the World Federation of Societies of Anaesthesiologists (WFSA).<ref name=CAS>{{cite web|url=http://www.cas.ca/English/Griffith|author=J Earl Wynands|title=Harold Randall Griffith, MD, CM, OC - 1894-1985|publisher=Canadian Anesthesiologists' Society |accessdate=2012-03-21}}</ref>

To supplement his medical degree, he studied [[homeopathy]] at the [[Hahnemann Medical College]] in Philadelphia. He joined his father in private practice, specialising in anaesthetics and on his death in 1936 succeeded him as medical director of the Montreal Homeopathic Hospital (in 1951 renamed Queen Elizabeth Hospital, Montreal), where he was noted for the precision of his clinical records.  His brother James Griffith, medical doctor|was also a medical doctor, surgeon in chief at the same hospital from 1937 to 1966.{{cn|date=March 2012}}

He introduced use of [[ethylene]] (1923) and [[cyclopropane]] (1933) into Canadian anaesthetic practice.<ref name=CAS/>
On January 23, 1942, with resident [[Enid Johnson Macleod|Enid Johnson]], he used [[curare]] for the first time during anesthesia to produce muscle relaxation in human patients undergoing surgery.<ref>{{cite journal |first1=Charles |last1=Czarnowski |first2=Jason |last2=Bailey |month=September |year=2007 |title=Curare and a Canadian connection |journal=Canadian Family Physician |volume=53 |issue=9 |pages=1531–2 |url=http://www.cfp.ca/cgi/content/full/53/9/1531 |pmc=2234642 |pmid=}}</ref>

==Recognition==
McGill University established the Harold R Griffith Research Chair in Anesthesia in 1992.<ref name=CAS/>

